title: John Porch
text:
John Porch (born 4 March 1994) is an Australian professional <a href="rugby%20union">rugby union</a> player, currently playing for Irish side <a href="Connacht%20Rugby">Connacht</a>.
Porch joined Irish province <a href="Connacht%20Rugby">Connacht</a>, who compete in the <a href="Pro14">Pro14</a> and <a href="European%20Rugby%20Champions%20Cup">European Rugby Champions Cup</a>, ahead of the 2019–20 <a href="Northern%20Hemisphere">northern hemisphere</a> season. Connacht's current head coach is former <a href="Australia%20national%20rugby%20sevens%20team">Australia 7s</a> head coach <a href="Andy%20Friend">Andy Friend</a>.
Australia.
Porch represented Australia at the <a href="2016%20Summer%20Olympics">2016 Rio Olympics</a>.
He represented Australia at the 2018 Gold Coast Commonwealth Games for the Australian Sevens.
